"publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"41 g","fat":"40.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"81 g","calories":"3644 kJ \/ 870 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, frying pan, grill, hob","hintsAndTricks":["This recipe uses shop-bought naan bread for a quicker meal, but if time allows, make your own naan in your Thermomix®. See <i>A Taste of India<\/i> for recipes.","This fun dinner is a cross between a chicken tikka masala and a pizza! Chicken thigh pieces are stirred through a flavourful tikka sauce, then spooned onto fluffy naan breads before being placed under the grill for a few minutes to brown. Topped with fresh coriander and tangy yoghurt, these flatbreads are a delicious, family-friendly alternative to a traditional curry."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","45m","4 portions"]}